<MELItem itemNbr="49-11-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-49-11-01.1.2-49-11-01_FAA">
<Title>Auxiliary Power Unit (APU)</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="1" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Left AGCU operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>VFSG systems operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO beyond 180 minutes is not conducted.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>A VFSG system is considered to be operating normally if its associated status message (ELEC GEN SYS L1, L2, R1 or R2) is not displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>If desired, the APU may be deactivated by opening and collaring P49 panel circuit breakers APUC-1, ACTR-APU INLET DR, and APU FUEL CTRL.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>The APU may be removed by installing dispatch tool K49003</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Ground Power Engine Start is not allowed if either associated ELEC ENGINE STARTER status message is displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceNote>
<OperationProcedure>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Flight must remain within 180 minutes of landing at a suitable airport.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Start the first engine using the Ground Power Engine Start Supplementary Procedure. Ground Power Engine Start is not allowed if either associated ELEC ENGINE STARTER status message is displayed.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>